article.headline: Quinnipiac 70, LIU 68
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Chris Wehye's layup with 6 seconds to play closed out an 8-0 run that gave Quinnipiac a 70-68 win over LIU on Saturday. The Bobcats (12-12, 10-5 Northeast Conference) tied it at 68 on DeMario Anderson's layup with 30 seconds remaining. LIU's Jaytornah Wisseh then turned the ball over, setting the stage for Wehye's shot. LIU's Tyrone Mattison missed a layup at the buzzer. James Williams led the Blackbirds (9-17, 5-10) with 19 points, including the 3-pointer that gave them a 68-62 lead with 1:54 to go. Anderson and Adam Gonzalez added 16 points apiece for Quinnipiac.
